sentences.sContent: ...the mighty sea power of the Anglo-Saxons.
sentences.sCn: ...盎格鲁撒克逊人的强大海权。

sentences.sContent: ...the grave of an early Anglo-Saxon king.
sentences.sCn: ...一位早期盎格鲁撒克逊国王的坟墓。

trans.tranOther: someone who belonged to the race of people who lived in England from about 600 AD
The Anglo-Saxon period is the period of English history from the fifth century AD to the Norman Conquest in 1066
